sections.comments: HIST 273 will introduce students to the methods of historical practice, including primary-source analysis, historical writing, library and research skills, and public history.HIST 273 will be taught asynchronously. Students will not be expected to participate in class activities during the stated class hours.

description: Societies, cultures, and politics of the Indian subcontinent from its ancient civilizations to the formation of the modern nation-states of South Asia.
